{
  "text": "Noninvasive transthoracic echocardiography was performed on anesthetized mice by using isoflurane (1% to 1.5%) as described previously. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] A Vevo 770 high-resolution imaging system equipped with a 30-MHz transducer (RMV-707B; VisualSonics, Toronto, ON, Canada) was used, and systolic and diastolic cardiac functions were analyzed. Systolic function was assessed using B-mode and motion (M)-mode images of echocardiography.",
